race.comment: Competitive. MY UNCLE DID IT (8) was unlucky not to have won in her maiden preparation but made amends at Hamilton first-up over 1400m. The step up to the mile suits, and in 56 grade, she can take the next step for the Wilde yard. RICKY RUNS (9) was beaten a whisker at this level on the same day over 1400m. The extra metres won't bother, and he's a second-up winner with solid each-way claims. THINXZO (3) hasn't been too far away since his Geelong Maiden win. This is easier, and he can make the finish again. SWITCH HIT (4) disappointed when backed off the map at Corowa, but his win at Bendigo this grade/trip prior reads well enough. He will be hitting the line, and is a decent chance to bounce.
